Text.Value: Bet the hag who ripped my eye out is howling from the grave.
Glorious. And they gave you some handsome scars.
Prove it. Who's singing your name?
Always special when it's just for your ears alone, ain't it?
I took someone's eye out for spilling my drink in the war camps last night. Don't prove nothing.
That was you? I heard Ragzlin was tough as dragon meat.
The sinners who've fallen in the face of righteous justice.
Forgotten glades and eternal streams whisper their protector's name.
Those I am sworn to protect.
Those who'd bind another to their will whisper my name in nightmares.
I do not peddle. I put weapons in worthy hands.
Either buy something, or leave.
Hah! Bark, bark. Like a worg pup, you are.
Thought I smelt something... outlandish about you. Very well.
Mercy, mercy, please - I might just wet myself.

EditorData.NodeContext: Patronising guffaw at our threat - next lines goes to flat, abrupt threat

Text.Value: Your tone is asking for a beating, bugbear.
Thought so. Lucky you're with the Absolute or I'd sell you nothin'.
Leave.
I'll give you that. Songs lie, flesh can't - and you look plenty battle-worn.
Hah! So there's a little spice to go with all that strange.

EditorData.NodeContext: No innuendo - just commenting approvingly on Lae'zel's boast / looks

Text.Value: Magic with a bite, eh? That's worth a chorus of blood and bone.
If you have coin, then show it.

EditorData.NodeContext: suspicious, weighing up the person he's greeting

Text.Value: A hag? Now that's an ugly and glorious song.

EditorData.NodeContext: impressed - just heard that you killed a hag

Text.Value: To mock me is to beg for death.
You're certain they weren't just falling asleep?
What do you have on offer?
Took a liking to you, did she? Watch yourself - she breaks her toys once she's done with them.
I have cut from corpses a thousand tongues, and those thousand tongues sing of murder.
Check the calluses on my hands. Those come only from a steadfast grip on a weapon.
That was you? Hells, I'll sing your name myself for that.
That so? Heard that was a traitor, myself.
Nobody sings my name - I don't leave any witnesses.
The only god who holds power here is the Absolute - remember that.
The bridge to glory is built on the bones of the dead.
The Absolute needs warriors for Her crusade. But I see only weaklings in this place.

EditorData.NodeContext: Faintly disgusted - he looks around and sees typically 'non-monstrous' races - the kind his people usually prey on

Text.Value: You seek arms? I seek a warrior worthy to bear them.

EditorData.NodeContext: gruff greeting to somebody he doesn't respect

Text.Value: The Absolute is. I burned that druids' grove to the ground.
Normally talk like that's empty - but there's something behind those words of yours. I can feel it.
Well, now - looks like there's something swinging beneath those robes after all.
Screaming my name, more like. I know how to inflict pain. Show respect, or I'll give you a demonstration.
People must scare easy where you're from. I don't.
Doubt you've done anything worth witnessing.

EditorData.NodeContext: using the word 'witnessing' in response to a player saying they don't leave witnesses

Text.Value: Shame I'm not selling aloe, then - keep your ugly hands to yourself.
You know - I think I recognise you. And I still can't remember your name.

EditorData.NodeContext: Leading us on for a moment - second half is the put down.

Text.Value: The demons of the abyss sing my name and tremble.
Open shop, or it will be you howling my name and begging my mercies.
If your stomach's strong enough, I'll tell you how I lost this eye.
The Weave itself - for I traverse its depths with the ease of breathing.
Just show me what you have.
No songs. Just screams.
Nobody sings my name - I don't leave any witnesses.
Oh, no one sings it. But hundreds have died sobbing with my name on their lips.
Say no more. An eye's a hard thing to lose - worth a chorus of blood and bone.

EditorData.NodeContext: impressed by the wound he was just shown in a 'you should see the other guy' kinda context

Text.Value: Big talk from a little girl. And I believe every word.
Hrrr. Looks like there's bite in you yet.

EditorData.NodeContext: amused - just got threatened and was impressed by the bravery of the person threatening him

Text.Value: Want anything from my stash, you pay less than the rest.
Footprints in untrodden places sing my travels and trials.
Perhaps 'warrior' isn't the right word. But I could turn this tower to dust without twitching my finger.
You'll never peddle your wares with that attitude.
No one.
Whole lot of talk, and still you've managed to say nothing.
That might have been a pretty slaughter, but I heard Minthara led the attack.

EditorData.NodeContext: dismissing a claim to glory he just heard - and Minthara will have 'a lament' because she's about to be sent for execution

Text.Value: The gods - when I slit my enemies' throats and offer their lives up as tribute.
Those who bathe in the warmth and light of the one I serve.
Friends and enemies alike - for I wield the power of the divine with the ease of breathing.
You want a warrior? Here I am.
You'll be shrieking my name if you keep asking inane questions.
Looks like a demon chewed you up and spat you out. You couldn't make a goblin tremble.
And they're singing, are they? Strange, all I hear is self-righteous horsecack.
Don't provoke me - I have a short temper.
Get moving, will you?
Dror Ragzlin isn't. I ripped him and his camp apart.
Well, I mainly do the singing. Usually while beating my foes to a pulp - it's quite the sight.
The bastards who took my eye aren't singing. They're screaming in the Hells.
The Absolute's war drums beat loud in your chest. How may I serve?

EditorData.NodeContext: warm greeting to a person he respects

Text.Value: Depends on what my magic summons - could be anything from a cow to a mephit. But they're all very musical, I assure you.
My dragonblood sings every time I burn an enemy alive.
The skies themselves - when they bow to my magic and unleash a tidal wave of power.
Slaughter well, True Soul.
Nature's beasts - with fangs of fury and unsheathed claw.
Leave.
Check my knuckles - I've felled plenty of foes with my fists alone.
Bookish nobodies are of no interest to me.
Respect is earned, elf. Not offered up to them as stamp their foot for it.
Z'rell said you're to share her private stash with me.

Synopsis: A merchant selling in the bazaar on the ground floor of Moonrise Tower. He is a passionate bugbear who believes only the strongest should enjoy the Absolute's spoils. Players can earn his respect for a discount.
